{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"@objc","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"subscribeToUpdates","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"_","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"update","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": @","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"@escaping","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ([","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:8BrazeKit0A0C6BannerC","text":"Banner","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/Banner"},{"text":"]) -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s4Voida","text":"Void","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@M@BrazeKit@objc(cs)Braze","text":"Braze","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze"},{"text":".","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:8BrazeKit0A0C11CancellableC","text":"Cancellable","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/Cancellable"}],"platforms":["iOS"]}]},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The update handler executed on the main thread with the latest banners."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"update"}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"return-value","text":"Return Value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A cancellable. You must keep a strong reference to the cancellable to keep the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"subscription active. The subscription is automatically cancelled when the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"cancellable is deinitialized. Alternatively, you can call"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/Cancellable\/cancel()"},{"type":"text","text":" to cancel the subscription."}]}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If a banner sync has already succeeded in the current session, the update handler is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"invoked once with the current banners as an initial replay snapshot. The replay is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"scheduled on the view-store queue and dispatched to main from there, so the handler","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is always invoked ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"after","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"subscribeToUpdates(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" returns — never inline on the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"calling thread. The replay is delivered at most once, and is suppressed if a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"delegate-driven update lands on the subscriber first.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Subscribes to banners updates."}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/brazekit\/braze\/banners-swift.class\/subscribetoupdates(_:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit","doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze","doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/Banners-swift.class"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/Banners-swift.class\/subscribeToUpdates(_:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:8BrazeKit0A0C7BannersC18subscribeToUpdatesyAC11CancellableCySDySSAC6BannerCGScMYccF","mo